column2: WARM UP - Any warm up is appropriate, unless you have an unique individual circumstance
REST DAYS - In a perfect world, have a rest day after day 2 and 4
REST TIMES - Rest times for all exercises are a 3 minute minimum. For strength, it doesnt matter how much longer this goes, so long as you stay warm
UNSURE OF AN EXERCISE - All exercises can be googled as they are written. Don't get caught up in minutia, there are more right ways to do an exercise than wrong ways to do an exercise
SUPERSETS - When 2 exercises are listed without a space between them, this is a superset
NOMENCLATURE - SA = single arm, DB = dumbbell, BB = barbell, SL = single leg
RECORDING LOADS - Input loads into week one load column and progressions will appear for the following weeks. You can record loads over the top of these as you do them
ROUNDING - Loads are prescibed using a mathematical equation so use discretion to round up, or down. You have the freedom to choose a number slightly higher or slightly lower
RPE - is for your FINAL SET. You will fatigue, so allow for this
